  "explanations": {
    "methodology": "A rule-based scorecard was constructed using only pre-loan available features. Six risk factors (credit score, loan-to-income ratio, age, employment years, debt-to-income ratio, region) are scored with interpretable point values. The total score maps to four risk levels. No machine learning model was trained.",
    "why_rule_based": "The dataset has only 8 rows, far too few for any statistical or ML model. A transparent, deterministic scorecard is the only viable approach.",
    "leakage_handling": "'post_loan_collection_calls' is explicitly excluded as it is a post-loan field. 'default_90d' is the target variable and is not used as a pre-loan feature."
  },
